OL,7,FEarlier this year, the Independent
OL,8,FOffice for Police Conduct (IOPC) told
OL,9,Ffamilies and survivors their
OL,10,Finvestigation had found South
OL,11,FYorkshire Police sought to deflect the
OL,12,Fblame from themselves.
OL,14,FBut the police watchdog said it was
OL,15,Funable to find that officers had a
OL,16,Fcase to answer for misconduct because
OL,17,Fthe professional standards for
OL,18,Fpolicing at the time did not include a
OL,19,Fspecific duty of candour.
